physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Gynecological examination revealed watery discharge from the vagina, thickening of the cervix with a diameter of approximately 4.5 cm, hardness, and positive blood on palpation. The uterine body was the size of a two-month pregnancy, and thickening was noted in the left adnexal area. Trimanual examination showed bilateral paracervical ligaments without palpable nodules or contractures, elastic, and smooth rectal mucosa.
